  ('HOD102', 88, 'This picture reveals an urban-planning proposal designed by Antonio Sant''Elia (1914), in which the author argued for the abolishment of decoration and for transcience in design and architecture. What style did he follow?', '{"A":"The Aesthetic Movement","B":"De Sijl.","C":"Constructivism.","D":"Futurism."}'::jsonb, 'D', 'D. Futurism.', '[{"id":"learninghub/questions/huglofj3les4w8ycb92g","src":"https://res.cloudinary.com/ddc4uvm7m/image/upload/v1782571943/learninghub/questions/huglofj3les4w8ycb92g.webp","url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/ddc4uvm7m/image/upload/v1782571943/learninghub/questions/huglofj3les4w8ycb92g.webp","width":140,"format":"webp","height":208,"source":"cloudinary","public_id":"learninghub/questions/huglofj3les4w8ycb92g"}]'::jsonb, true, true, 'low', null),
