  ('HOD102', 140, 'What is the role of the Biomimicry design?', '{"A":"The utilitarian approach made sense commercially in a society where middle-class consumers preferred a stylish, sculptural look too bland rationalism.","B":"Might offer design solutions to all sorts of ecological problems, from the development of sustainable water schemes to the construction of buildings that store carbon emissions.","C":"The design solution is used to recycle scrap to create fashionable and functional artefacts for the home and office.","D":"It has promoted the rise of biomorphism, which, rather than attempting to capture the abstracted essence of natural forms, distorted them for purely decorative purposes."}'::jsonb, 'B', 'B. Might offer design solutions to all sorts of ecological problems, from the development of sustainable water schemes to the construction of buildings that store carbon emissions.', '[]'::jsonb, true, false, 'low', null),
