  ('HOD102', 143, 'In 1959, the Left-leaning Nation magazine published an article named "The Safe Car You Can''t Buy", in which the author stated the ethical issues surrounding design, manufacture, consumer protection & first attack on safety measures in car design and manufacturing. Who is the author of this article? Check one option.', '{"A":"Joe Colombo.","B":"Victor Papanek.","C":"Ralph Nader .","D":"Verner Panton."}'::jsonb, 'C', 'C. Ralph Nader .', '[]'::jsonb, true, false, 'low', null),
  ('HOD102', 144, 'Fill in the blank The Italian modern design in 1920 and 1930 was the first cultural movement to distance itself from nature and instead glorify the energetic flux of the metropolis. To this end, ..... designers such as Fortunato Depero used fragmented cubistic forms as a means of evoking acceleration and speed. Check one option.', '{"A":"Futurist","B":"Art Deco","C":"Bauhaus","D":"Rococo"}'::jsonb, 'A', 'A. Futurist', '[]'::jsonb, true, false, 'low', null),
  ('HOD102', 145, 'Who was seen as a true Renaissance man or as innovative designer thinker who during his life time was admired as much for his work not only in fine art but also his ability to conceptualize revolutionary designs helped to raise the status of design practice? Check one option.', '{"A":"Michelangelo.","B":"Johann Gutenberg.","C":"Leonardo da Vinci.","D":"Hans Vredeman de Vries."}'::jsonb, 'C', 'C. Leonardo da Vinci.', '[]'::jsonb, true, false, 'low', null),
