  ('HOD102', 171, 'The book that fundamentally altered the design community''s approach to the environment. Its authors, William McDonough and Michael Braungart highlighted the waste and destruction wrought when consumer products are made, used, and then discarded. What is the name of this book?', '{"A":"Whole Earth Catalog, spring (1969).","B":"Human Ecology and Social Change (1971)","C":"Cradle to Cradle: Remaking the Way We Make Things (2002)","D":"The Upcycle: Beyond Sustainability - Designing (2013)"}'::jsonb, 'C', 'C. Cradle to Cradle: Remaking the Way We Make Things (2002)', '[]'::jsonb, true, false, 'low', null),
  ('HOD102', 172, 'What are the characteristics of the Mannerist style?', '{"A":"Mobility techniques need gravel lobby, try to make the mind sticking high. They worship bizarre beauty, shape language in an unusual way.","B":"Heavy and floral, dramatic, full of emotion.","C":"Elective, feminine, sumptuous, rich and decorative in Europe.","D":"Ignoring the futility of Rococo, inspired by classical Greek and Roman art, emphasizing simplicity and balance, is the bridge for the birth of the Industrial Revolution."}'::jsonb, 'A', 'A. Mobility techniques need gravel lobby, try to make the mind sticking high. They worship bizarre beauty, shape language in an unusual way.', '[]'::jsonb, true, false, 'low', null),
