  ('HOD102', 174, 'In the early 20th century, why were German manufacturers reluctant to accept partial mechanization of certain production processes but still considered it a necessary evil?', '{"A":"They believe that machines can produce low quality products at high prices..","B":"They still hold the belief that machines are difficult to use.","C":"They still hold the belief that machines take away people''s jobs and that the products they make are bad.","D":"They still kept the belief that the machine could not create high-quality products"}'::jsonb, 'D', 'D. They still kept the belief that the machine could not create high-quality products', '[]'::jsonb, true, false, 'low', null),
